Aquaserv SA, a Romanian water
utility, is seeking bids for a 41 million-lei ($12 million)
contract to upgrade water and sewage networks in the center of
the country, a European Union procurement  document  showed.  The utility plans to build a water treatment plant in the
town of Ludus and another one in Iernut, while also expanding
the water and sewage networks in both, according to the
statement. Bids can be submitted by June 28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
